# Spec Sync Rule

When you finish an edit to a component, page, or workflow file, check if the change is one of these types:

- Layout changes (structure, positioning, new/removed UI sections)
- Workflow changes (new user flow, changed step order, new states)
- Color/theme changes (design tokens, palette, styling intent — not one-off Tailwind class tweaks)
- User-facing text changes (copy, labels, headings, error messages shown to users)

If the change matches one of the above:

1. Find the spec file at `docs/specs/{feature-name}.md` matching the feature this file belongs to. If none exists, create one using `docs/specs/_template.md` as the structure.
2. Update only the relevant section (Layout, Workflow, Visual/Style, or Copy) — don't rewrite the whole doc, don't add commentary about the update itself.
3. Bump "Last updated" to today's date.

Do NOT touch spec files for:

- Bug fixes
- Refactors (renaming, extracting functions, type fixes)
- Performance changes
- Dependency/config updates
- Test changes

If unsure whether a change is spec-worthy, don't touch the spec file — mention it in your response instead.
